{"id":71,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":71,"title":"Amalek, Amalekites","subtitle":"","short_title":"Amalek, Amalekites","uri":"/scriptures/bd/amalek","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/amalek.t1","order":".000.188"},[".title","Amalek, Amalekites"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/amalek.p1","order":".000.189"},"An Arab tribe that lived in the desert of Paran between the Arabah and the Mediterranean and at one time seem to have ranged as far north as Mount Ephraim (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/judg/5.14"},"Judg. 5:14"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/judg/12.15"},"12:15"],"). The Amalekites were at constant war with the Hebrews from the time of Moses (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/17.8"},"Ex. 17:8"],", etc.) till their power was broken by Saul and David (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/15"},"1 Sam. 15"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/27.8"},"27:8"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/30"},"30"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/8.12"},"2 Sam. 8:12"],"), and their last remnant was destroyed by the Simeonites (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-chr/4.43"},"1 Chr. 4:43"],")."]]],"refs":null}
